pan><hr size=1> Crosspost from KGC on current official actions.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well, I am back now and spent quite a while re-reading these boards and the various threads that were on it over the past couple of days.<br>
To me, there is only one real, viable response (at this time). It is the same one that was used when EW, SS, RLs etc decide to try FFA on Karana:<br>
<br>
1) The existing rotations shall remain in place.<br>
<br>
2) Guilds are allowed to get outside help from *any* guild on Karana to kill their target mob in a timely manner. No sanctions shall be applied to a guild seeking outside help. Edit: This is only for the duration of the current situation.<br>
<br>
3) All Guilds taking part in the KGC are strongly encouraged to help other guilds in taking down a large mob when they are asked to help. They should turn all loot over to the guild that is currently up for the large mob, and the rotation will move along. <br>
<br>
4) It is the responsibility of the guild that is up for the MOB to watch for it. Durn it, if you are up - get support there ASAP or you will be part of the problem.<br>
<br>
5) I would recommend forming a KGC chat channel. No need to password protect it, since any password would most likely be given to those we do not want to have it. Willing guild leaders should join and watch. Check who is on there before communicating and use it to muster forces quickly if needed.<br>
<br>
6) Do not count on the &quot;uber&quot; guilds for help. Some of them may well be willing to help, but some will not. It is going to be up to the mid and smaller guilds on Karana to drive this forward. It is really up to you to preserve the KGC rotations through your actions. <br>
<br>
7) At this time, no sanctions shall be taken against Nightbane, and their guild officers shall retain access to these boards. If their guild members continue to kill KGC targets in early January - then sanctions may be considered and implemented quickly. They are strongly encouraged to clean up the mess being caused by some of their guild members.<br>
<br>
(Note: I will lock this thread if it turns into a Nightbane discussion at this time.)<br>
<br>
