<br>
I think not.<br>
<br>
The KGC works for one reason and one reason only.  Both the large and small guilds are willing to work together because frankly we ALL have better things to do than to sit around a zone training Sev over everyone.  If you think FFA would be such a great idea, fork over the 50 bucks and move over to Mith Marr and play with the big boys.<br>
<br>
Nightbane?  Nightbane is not an uber guild.  Karana has no uber guild in the Fires of Heaven or Afterlife sense of the word.  Just because they can field 1 or 2 groups to keep 10 or so rotations down doesnt mean they're uber.  A true uber guild can keep every named mob from Kunark on through Luclin perma killed, while still blowing through the Tier 2 and 3 and 4 planes in PoP.  At the same time.<br>
<br>
Thats an uber guild.<br>
<br>
Nightbane is simply the largest of the large guilds on Karana.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because with the KGC there's simply no need to a single uber guild to form.  We can act civil to each other, and work together here.  You know, in a mature adult fashion.<br>
<br>
Yes, there are downsides.  In this case you cannot simply take a target whenever you want to, and you do sacrafice a lot of time between hits.  Although that is getting addressed.<br>
<br>
I would point out, many of the largers guilds have been the reason the KGC hasnt changed.  They simply like things the way they are.  Keeping the status quo benefits only the larger guilds for the most part.  And they know it.<br>
<br>
You can call it whatever you want.  Karana is the one server in the game where you can say that if you wait long enough, you'll eventually get what you want.  On any other server you have 1 choice.  Join an uber guild.  Its that simple.  You think you could compete with one of them in an FFA situation?<br>
<br>
Yeah.<br>
<br>
Whatever.<br>
<br>
