<br>
Even though he hasnt played the game in well over a year.  They remember.<br>
<br>
Why?  Because both the Silver Daggers and KCoG were his legacy.  It was founded upon respect of others and fairness always.<br>
<br>
I'm sure you could say it doesnt really matter as its just a game and who cares what others think of you in 10 years.  And to an extent thats true.  But then, who cares about honor and integrity and sense of duty?  Those things too only really mean anything to you.  And yet they too are important because they are what define you.  When you are true to yourself others recognize that and respect it.<br>
<br>
And in the end thats what people like Dazz and Zfalcon simply cant stand.  They cannot stand, as the bully in school couldnt, seeing others being better than themselves simply by helping others.  They understood at a deeper level that strength of character was something they couldnt beat and they resented that in those that had it.<br>
<br>
Call it whatever you like, but I ask this of everyone here.<br>
<br>
What will your legacy be? Will it be one of tolerance and respect to others?  Or will it simply be one of selfishness and greed.<br>
<br>
The choice is yours and yours alone.  No one can make it for you or force it upon you.  <br>
<br>
Yes, I admit I feel jealous and even hate it when people start linking items I dont have and want and will never see because I choose my path.  I hate it when I see a druid walking around offering to sell a Cowl of Mortality.  I hate knowing I've never had more than 3kpp in the bank because I dont farm and pass on rolls in favor of others who might use it.<br>
<br>
