<br>
One day when I leave EQ people will remember me.  People who I never met, people who didnt know me really.  People will remember my guild and KCoG and smile.  When I leave EQ I will leave knowing I made the EQ experience better for many people and never by stepping on someone else.  There are many other people, on the other side of these monitors, who will remember.  And I will have made a difference.<br>
<br>
Now what does all this have to do with the KGC?  Pretty much nothing, except that it all starts with you.  Dont worry what others think.  Dont worry about what others do.  Worry only about what you are doing.  Everything else will take care of itself.<br>
<br>
Be fair, respect others, and do the right thing even if its not the right thing for you, and even the KGC will begin to make sense.<br>
<br>
Dont, and you simply become part of the problem instead of the solution.<br>
<br>
The choice is yours.  What will you stand for?<br>
